<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q19_v15" title="Q19_v15" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float"><qti-default-value><qti-value>0</qti-value></qti-default-value></qti-outcome-declaration><qti-item-body>
    <p>En un cálculo intermedio se obtiene el siguiente producto:</p>
    <p>
      <m:math>
        <m:mrow>
          <m:mn>4</m:mn>
          <m:mo>·</m:mo>
          <m:msqrt>
            <m:mn>10</m:mn>
          </m:msqrt>
          <m:mo>·</m:mo>
          <m:mo>(</m:mo>
          <m:mo>-</m:mo>
          <m:mn>2</m:mn>
          <m:mo>)</m:mo>
        </m:mrow>
      </m:math>
    </p>
    <p>¿Cuál es la forma simplificada de esta expresión?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" max-choices="1">
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>4</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                <m:mn>20</m:mn>
              </m:mrow>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El producto se simplifica multiplicando primero los factores fuera de la raíz: 4 · (−2) = −8, por lo que resulta −8√10. En cambio, 4√−20 no es una forma equivalente en los números reales, porque la raíz cuadrada de un número negativo no es real.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>8</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! Se multiplican los factores numéricos 4 y −2: 4 · (−2) = −8. El factor √10 se mantiene, así que la expresión queda −8√10.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mo>-</m:mo>
            <m:mn>8</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>5</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. Al multiplicar 4 · (−2) se obtiene −8, pero el radical original es √10 y no puede cambiarse a √5. La expresión correcta es −8√10, no −8√5.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
      
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">
        <m:math>
          <m:mrow>
            <m:mn>8</m:mn>
            <m:msqrt>
              <m:mn>10</m:mn>
            </m:msqrt>
          </m:mrow>
        </m:math>
        <qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. El valor absoluto 8 es correcto porque 4 · 2 = 8, pero el signo no. Como uno de los factores es negativo, 4 · (−2) = −8. Por eso la expresión simplificada es −8√10.</qti-feedback-inline>
      </qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Simplificación del producto con raíz cuadrada</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Identificar los factores</strong></p>
            <p>La expresión dada es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Sus factores son 4, <m:math><m:msqrt><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:math> y −2.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Multiplicar los números enteros</strong></p>
            <p>Primero se multiplican los factores numéricos:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mn>4</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>(</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>2</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>)</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Como un número positivo por un número negativo da negativo, el resultado es −8.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Mantener el radical</strong></p>
            <p>El factor <m:math><m:msqrt><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:math> no se modifica, porque no hay otro radical con el cual combinarlo.</p>
            <p>Entonces queda:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Comparar con las alternativas</strong></p>
            <p>La única opción que coincide exactamente con el resultado obtenido es:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mo>-</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>8</m:mn>
                  <m:msqrt>
                    <m:mn>10</m:mn>
                  </m:msqrt>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La forma simplificada de la expresión es <m:math><m:mrow><m:mo>-</m:mo><m:mn>8</m:mn><m:msqrt><m:mn>10</m:mn></m:msqrt></m:mrow></m:math>, por lo tanto la alternativa correcta es la <strong>B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>